<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Adding new analytics to the budget app lines in CB 2.0</title>
</head>
<body>

<div>
    <h2 id='pageTop'>SOM Adding New Analytics Guide</h2>
    <hr/>
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <ol>
        <li>Go to the Main Configurator and click on “CB Dimensions”<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Click on the “Create New” button<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Specify the “Name” and “Page Header” fields then click “Save”<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Click the “Displayed on Home” checkbox and then click “Save”. Make sure the “Custom Mode” checkboxes are not selected<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Go back to the Main Configurator and refresh the page, make sure the new dimension is in the list. Click on the “Budget App Amount” link<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Scroll down to the “Dimensions” section of the “Budget App Amount” dimension page and open the accordion<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Select the needed dimension in any available (empty) line, change the title if needed, and click “Visible”<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Scroll back to the top of the page and click “Save”<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Go back to the CB Dimensions in Main Configurator and repeat the actions from steps 6 - 8 for the “budget App Template” dimension<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Go to the Homepage and click on the new dimension link in the “Data Links” panel<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Click “Add New”, specify the name of the record and click “Save”<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Now you can use this dimension in budget apps<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
    </ol>

</div>
<br/>

<br/>
<hr/>


<button onclick="topFunction()" id="myBtn" title="Go to top">Top</button>

<script>
    let mybutton = document.getElementById("myBtn");
    window.onscroll = function () {
        scrollFunction()
    };

    function scrollFunction() {
        mybutton.style.display = document.body.scrollTop > 20 || document.documentElement.scrollTop > 20 ? "block" : "none";
    }

    function topFunction() {
        document.body.scrollTop = 0;
        document.documentElement.scrollTop = 0;
    }
</script>

<style>
    #myBtn {
        display: none;
        position: fixed;
        bottom: 20px;
        right: 30px;
        z-index: 99;
        font-size: 18px;
        border: 1px solid #b5e853;
        outline: none;
        background-color: #171717;
        color: #b5e853;
        cursor: pointer;
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    #myBtn:hover {
        background-color: #181818;
    }
</style>

</body>
</html>
